title: Does DeepExplainer work with Lambda layers?
body:
Hi, I have implemented a variational LSTM autoencoder for a multivariate time series task and I am having some issues using DeepExplainer. First of all I will provide a summary of the model that I am using:

This is the summary of the autoencoder:
![vae](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37838057/67770986-bbb7e280-fa57-11e9-8dd1-693b1d8da378.PNG)

And this is the summary of the encoder:
![encoder](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37838057/67771071-db4f0b00-fa57-11e9-9555-022cadcccbbd.PNG)

So,with the encoder  I am extracting 50 features form each 30x15 input data and I want to measure the importance that each input data has in the extracted features. So, I have tried to apply DeepExplainer on the encoder like this:
![shap_code](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37838057/67771524-bf983480-fa58-11e9-9eba-7b12a44a2ef5.PNG)
And I am getting this error:
![err](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37838057/67771613-e5bdd480-fa58-11e9-922a-d3289fc58bab.PNG)
Does the DeepExplainer work with Lambda layers? I am using the lambda layer just for adding the activations of two layers.
